<br>
It's the 'true' sequel to Secret of Mana (SNES). Since it never made it in North America, US Square had to make another sequel to SOM, Secret of Evermore. <br>
<br>
The game is short, but the replay value is quite high. There are 6 characters, 3 you pick in the beginning to be in the story. The final boss depends on which main character is chosen. Not only that, each character has 4 final classes, making the characters even more fun to play.<br>
<br>
For example, Duran (swordsman) can become a Paladin (healing powers) or a Duelist (can imbue elemantal damage to weapons).<br>
<br>
You might be able to get the cartridge from EBay or Japan, but almost everyone I know who's played this used an emulator. <p>---<br>
